[
    {
        "text": "JAMES CLEWETT: Today's video is\ngoing to be all about the",
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 3.06
    },
    {
        "text": "National Lottery.",
        "start": 3.06,
        "duration": 0.98
    },
    {
        "text": "And if you're a number freak\nlike me, then the National",
        "start": 4.04,
        "duration": 3.29
    },
    {
        "text": "Lottery is great because it's\nthat two times a week when all",
        "start": 7.33,
        "duration": 3.975
    },
    {
        "text": "the people at home get\nto share in my",
        "start": 11.305,
        "duration": 3.115
    },
    {
        "text": "enthusiasm for numbers.",
        "start": 14.42,
        "duration": 1.45
    },
    {
        "text": "So what I want to do today is\ntalk a little bit about some",
        "start": 15.87,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "of the probabilities involved\nin the National lottery.",
        "start": 19.47,
        "duration": 2.93
    },
    {
        "text": "So before we start, I think we\nshould choose some numbers for",
        "start": 22.4,
        "duration": 2.99
    },
    {
        "text": "our lottery.",
        "start": 25.39,
        "duration": 0.47
    },
    {
        "text": "So our first number is going\nto be the number 14.",
        "start": 25.86,
        "duration": 2.86
    },
    {
        "text": "That's my birthday.",
        "start": 28.72,
        "duration": 0.79
    },
    {
        "text": "Then I think we'll have\nthe number 19.",
        "start": 29.51,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "That was a nice, good year\nfor me, 19 years old.",
        "start": 31.88,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "We'll have a few in the 30s--",
        "start": 34.48,
        "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
        "text": "31, and 33, and 34.",
        "start": 36.1,
        "duration": 4.49
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, and then one more, 45.",
        "start": 40.59,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "So I've chosen the number 14\nfor my birthday, the number",
        "start": 43.03,
        "duration": 2.98
    },
    {
        "text": "19, and then, a few in the 30s,\nnumber 31, 33, and 34,",
        "start": 46.01,
        "duration": 4.66
    },
    {
        "text": "and number 45.",
        "start": 50.67,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "So now, what are the odds of\nus picking those same six",
        "start": 52.2,
        "duration": 3.86
    },
    {
        "text": "balls out of our homemade\nlottery kit?",
        "start": 56.06,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "First of all, to start with,\nthere are six balls in here",
        "start": 58.56,
        "duration": 5.15
    },
    {
        "text": "which are winners for us.",
        "start": 63.71,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": "And there are 49 balls\njust like the",
        "start": 64.79,
        "duration": 1.93
    },
    {
        "text": "national lottery game.",
        "start": 66.72,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so I'm going to look away.",
        "start": 67.68,
        "duration": 2.43
    },
    {
        "text": "And I'm going to select.",
        "start": 70.11,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "And it's number 19,\na 6 out of 49.",
        "start": 73.47,
        "duration": 4.63
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so we put that\none to one side.",
        "start": 78.1,
        "duration": 1.89
    },
    {
        "text": "But now they're only 48 balls\nleft in the basket.",
        "start": 79.99,
        "duration": 3.57
    },
    {
        "text": "And we've got five winners\nleft in the box.",
        "start": 83.56,
        "duration": 2.89
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, let me give that\na good stir around.",
        "start": 86.45,
        "duration": 2.802
    },
    {
        "text": "And it's the number 45.",
        "start": 93.24,
        "duration": 2.53
    },
    {
        "text": "Put that one to one side, and\nagain, now, we've got one less",
        "start": 95.77,
        "duration": 2.86
    },
    {
        "text": "ball in the box.",
        "start": 98.63,
        "duration": 0.91
    },
    {
        "text": "So we're down to 47 balls and\njust four winners now.",
        "start": 99.54,
        "duration": 3.58
    },
    {
        "text": "Give them a good stir.",
        "start": 106.06,
        "duration": 4.42
    },
    {
        "text": "It's the number 31.",
        "start": 110.48,
        "duration": 1.19
    },
    {
        "text": "And that one, again, goes to\none side with our other",
        "start": 111.67,
        "duration": 2.03
    },
    {
        "text": "winning balls.",
        "start": 113.7,
        "duration": 0.89
    },
    {
        "text": "Just 46 balls left in here\nnow, and only 3 winners.",
        "start": 114.59,
        "duration": 2.66
    },
    {
        "text": "There it is.",
        "start": 121.77,
        "duration": 0.53
    },
    {
        "text": "The number 14.",
        "start": 122.3,
        "duration": 1.782
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, again, put that\none on one side.",
        "start": 124.082,
        "duration": 3.458
    },
    {
        "text": "Give ourselves a little stir.",
        "start": 127.54,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Now there's only 45 balls left\nand just two winners.",
        "start": 128.86,
        "duration": 8.475
    },
    {
        "text": "There it is.",
        "start": 137.335,
        "duration": 1.075
    },
    {
        "text": "The number 33.",
        "start": 138.41,
        "duration": 3.31
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so we've got one winning\nball left in the bucket.",
        "start": 141.72,
        "duration": 2.2
    },
    {
        "text": "So give it a stir.",
        "start": 143.92,
        "duration": 1.401
    },
    {
        "text": "There it is.",
        "start": 150.0,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "The number 34.",
        "start": 151.14,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so my chances of picking out\nthe number 34, were just 1",
        "start": 152.72,
        "duration": 2.97
    },
    {
        "text": "from 44 balls.",
        "start": 155.69,
        "duration": 3.33
    },
    {
        "text": "And there we have it.",
        "start": 159.02,
        "duration": 0.82
    },
    {
        "text": "What were the odds of me\nwinning the lottery and",
        "start": 159.84,
        "duration": 2.84
    },
    {
        "text": "retiring to become a part-time\nphysicist?",
        "start": 162.68,
        "duration": 2.97
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, let's have a look at it.",
        "start": 165.65,
        "duration": 2.17
    },
    {
        "text": "The chance of getting the first\nnumber was 6 in 49.",
        "start": 167.82,
        "duration": 3.72
    },
    {
        "text": "Then it's a completely\nindependent event, so we can",
        "start": 171.54,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "just multiply that by the chance\nof getting the second",
        "start": 174.3,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "number, which is 5 in 48.",
        "start": 177.0,
        "duration": 2.98
    },
    {
        "text": "So I can just just\nmultiply that.",
        "start": 179.98,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "Then we multiply that\nby the chance of",
        "start": 181.74,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "winning the third number--",
        "start": 183.45,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "the top line we can\ndo in our head--",
        "start": 184.74,
        "duration": 1.96
    },
    {
        "text": "is simply 720.",
        "start": 186.7,
        "duration": 4.44
    },
    {
        "text": "The bottom line--",
        "start": 191.14,
        "duration": 0.73
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm going to cheat--",
        "start": 191.87,
        "duration": 0.88
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm going to use a calculator.",
        "start": 192.75,
        "duration": 1.24
    },
    {
        "text": "49 times by 48 times by\n47 times by 46 times",
        "start": 193.99,
        "duration": 8.355
    },
    {
        "text": "by 45 times by 44.",
        "start": 202.345,
        "duration": 4.435
    },
    {
        "text": "And that's the number 10\nbillion and change.",
        "start": 206.78,
        "duration": 2.71
    },
    {
        "text": "So we're going to write down\nour 10 billion here.",
        "start": 209.49,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "So that gives us our final\nanswer in math speak, if you",
        "start": 212.28,
        "duration": 4.33
    },
    {
        "text": "like, of 7.151 times\n10 to the minus 8.",
        "start": 216.61,
        "duration": 9.08
    },
    {
        "text": "That number doesn't really mean\nanything to most of us.",
        "start": 225.69,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "And so I'm going to write\nthis as 1 over 13983816.",
        "start": 229.05,
        "duration": 14.59
    },
    {
        "text": "So the odds of winning the\nlottery are one part in",
        "start": 243.64,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "13,983,816.",
        "start": 245.86,
        "duration": 4.98
    },
    {
        "text": "Or in real money, about one\npart in 14 million.",
        "start": 250.84,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": "I play the lottery\nat Christmas.",
        "start": 253.75,
        "duration": 1.93
    },
    {
        "text": "Actually, I find it's been\nreally good fun.",
        "start": 255.68,
        "duration": 2.349
    },
    {
        "text": "So I tend to spend\nabout a fiver a",
        "start": 258.029,
        "duration": 1.761
    },
    {
        "text": "year on lottery numbers.",
        "start": 259.79,
        "duration": 2.239
    },
    {
        "text": "And for that one week that\nI've bought a ticket, I",
        "start": 262.029,
        "duration": 3.241
    },
    {
        "text": "daydream about all the really\ncool things that I'm going to",
        "start": 265.27,
        "duration": 3.34
    },
    {
        "text": "do if I win the lottery.",
        "start": 268.61,
        "duration": 1.04
    },
    {
        "text": "So how much is that worth?",
        "start": 269.65,
        "duration": 2.42
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't know.",
        "start": 272.07,
        "duration": 0.36
    },
    {
        "text": "I really enjoy it.",
        "start": 272.43,
        "duration": 0.92
    },
    {
        "text": "I really enjoy just\nthe process of",
        "start": 273.35,
        "duration": 1.97
    },
    {
        "text": "owning a lottery ticket.",
        "start": 275.32,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "But I know--",
        "start": 276.88,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm reasonably numerically\ngrounded--",
        "start": 278.02,
        "duration": 3.15
    },
    {
        "text": "I know that my chances\nof winning are very,",
        "start": 281.17,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "very close to zero.",
        "start": 283.21,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "I think my chances of being\nstruck by lightning are",
        "start": 284.35,
        "duration": 2.54
    },
    {
        "text": "something like seven times\nhigher than my chances of",
        "start": 286.89,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "winning the lottery.",
        "start": 289.49,
        "duration": 0.73
    },
    {
        "text": "So I'm kind of hoping\nthat doesn't happen.",
        "start": 290.22,
        "duration": 3.93
    },
    {
        "text": "So we've won the lottery.",
        "start": 294.15,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "We've matched six balls.",
        "start": 295.9,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": "That's absolutely fantastic.",
        "start": 297.16,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "But it doesn't really explain\nwhy every time I've bought a",
        "start": 298.41,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "lottery ticket, I've not matched\nany balls at all.",
        "start": 302.01,
        "duration": 3.15
    },
    {
        "text": "So what's the probability of\nbuying a lottery ticket and",
        "start": 305.16,
        "duration": 3.14
    },
    {
        "text": "matching no balls?",
        "start": 308.3,
        "duration": 0.82
    },
    {
        "text": "So let's go back to the numbers\nthat we selected.",
        "start": 309.12,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "So we had 14--",
        "start": 311.72,
        "duration": 2.74
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so this were our\nmagic numbers.",
        "start": 314.46,
        "duration": 3.1
    },
    {
        "text": "So what are the odds of\nselecting a first number which",
        "start": 317.56,
        "duration": 2.99
    },
    {
        "text": "doesn't match?",
        "start": 320.55,
        "duration": 0.51
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, there are 43 balls\nin there, out of",
        "start": 321.06,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "49 which don't match.",
        "start": 323.06,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "So I'm going to select one.",
        "start": 324.52,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "It's number 38.",
        "start": 328.96,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so that doesn't match.",
        "start": 331.48,
        "duration": 0.88
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't want that one.",
        "start": 332.36,
        "duration": 1.345
    },
    {
        "text": "Give it a stir.",
        "start": 333.705,
        "duration": 1.325
    },
    {
        "text": "Now remember, here we go.",
        "start": 335.03,
        "duration": 3.87
    },
    {
        "text": "That's the number 35.",
        "start": 338.9,
        "duration": 2.26
    },
    {
        "text": "And, again, it doesn't match.",
        "start": 341.16,
        "duration": 3.02
    },
    {
        "text": "Give them a stir.",
        "start": 344.18,
        "duration": 1.328
    },
    {
        "text": "It's the number 25.",
        "start": 348.79,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "Again, no use to me.",
        "start": 350.49,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "41 out of 47.",
        "start": 352.14,
        "duration": 2.97
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so the next one.",
        "start": 355.11,
        "duration": 1.474
    },
    {
        "text": "Number 23.",
        "start": 360.36,
        "duration": 0.996
    },
    {
        "text": "Getting a little annoyed\nwith this.",
        "start": 361.356,
        "duration": 1.874
    },
    {
        "text": "That's no good to me either.",
        "start": 363.23,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "So the chance of pulling\nout a nonwinner there",
        "start": 364.57,
        "duration": 2.98
    },
    {
        "text": "were 40 out of 46.",
        "start": 367.55,
        "duration": 3.66
    },
    {
        "text": "OK.",
        "start": 371.21,
        "duration": 1.236
    },
    {
        "text": "Do another one.",
        "start": 372.446,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "I've got the number 41.",
        "start": 377.459,
        "duration": 2.243
    },
    {
        "text": "No use.",
        "start": 379.702,
        "duration": 0.958
    },
    {
        "text": "OK.",
        "start": 380.66,
        "duration": 0.93
    },
    {
        "text": "So the chances, again--",
        "start": 381.59,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "39 out of 45.",
        "start": 383.81,
        "duration": 3.02
    },
    {
        "text": "And our last ball--",
        "start": 386.83,
        "duration": 2.411
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: Hang on, what do\nyou think it's going to be?",
        "start": 389.241,
        "duration": 1.949
    },
    {
        "text": "JAMES CLEWETT: Well,\nI don't think it's",
        "start": 391.19,
        "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
        "text": "going to be a winner.",
        "start": 392.81,
        "duration": 0.66
    },
    {
        "text": "That's for sure.",
        "start": 393.47,
        "duration": 1.352
    },
    {
        "text": "Uh, give it a stir.",
        "start": 394.822,
        "duration": 2.868
    },
    {
        "text": "I hope it's not a winner.",
        "start": 397.69,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "Number 43.",
        "start": 401.93,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so we've got no\nballs at all.",
        "start": 403.64,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "Rubbish.",
        "start": 405.56,
        "duration": 0.37
    },
    {
        "text": "Right.",
        "start": 405.93,
        "duration": 0.85
    },
    {
        "text": "The chances of a nonmatch--",
        "start": 406.78,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "38 out of 44.",
        "start": 408.86,
        "duration": 4.85
    },
    {
        "text": "If we calculate this number\nthrough-- again I'm going to",
        "start": 413.71,
        "duration": 3.02
    },
    {
        "text": "turn to my calculator.",
        "start": 416.73,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "OK?",
        "start": 421.82,
        "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
        "text": "So our probability of picking\nno matches whatsoever is 4",
        "start": 422.12,
        "duration": 6.95
    },
    {
        "text": "billion divided by 10\nbillion, which is--",
        "start": 429.07,
        "duration": 3.24
    },
    {
        "text": "sorry--",
        "start": 432.31,
        "duration": 0.71
    },
    {
        "text": "43%, 43.59649%.",
        "start": 433.02,
        "duration": 5.92
    },
    {
        "text": "Somebody is spending a pound\na week playing the lottery.",
        "start": 438.94,
        "duration": 3.32
    },
    {
        "text": "And for that pound a week,\nthey're getting hope and",
        "start": 442.26,
        "duration": 3.51
    },
    {
        "text": "excitement and a Saturday\nnight buzz.",
        "start": 445.77,
        "duration": 2.635
    },
    {
        "text": "I think that's great\nvalue to be honest.",
        "start": 448.405,
        "duration": 2.845
    },
    {
        "text": "So that's fine.",
        "start": 451.25,
        "duration": 0.8
    },
    {
        "text": "But if I hear of somebody who's\nspending 10, 20 quid a",
        "start": 452.05,
        "duration": 2.63
    },
    {
        "text": "week buying lottery\ntickets, stop.",
        "start": 454.68,
        "duration": 2.78
    },
    {
        "text": "Please stop.",
        "start": 457.46,
        "duration": 1.25
    }
]